RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 54. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.

CLAIM.OWNER: Mountain View Racing LLC and Golden Melinda B

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRUNK TEXT took an immediate lead and rated the pace inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and was kept alert through the stretch. UNCLE PRESS stalked the earlier pace from the three and four paths, bid leaving the three eighths pole, raced close off the rail on the far turn but proved no match in the stretch. COMEONTURNMELOOSE stalked from the three path, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and finished evenly to take third late stretch. CALLISTO'S BRIGADE stalked off the rail, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn then flattened inside the eighth pole. I SEE NOTHING saved ground, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. KING OF LUCK rounded the opening turn in the five path, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn and showed little more. SENZA STRIKE hesitated at least a full length leaving the gate then saved ground. Meetmarysman became fractious in the gate and was a late scratch.

ENTRY.NAME: Callisto's Brigade
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,chased 3/8,rail far turn,flattened lane

ENTRY.NAME: Uncle Press
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3& 4p,bid 3/8,close off rail turn,no match lane

ENTRY.NAME: King of Luck
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 18500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,0 00 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY SISTER PAM saved ground off the pace on the opening turn, started a bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, dug in from the head of the lane, took over just inside the sixteenth pole and edged clear later yards. TENNIS TAP was shut off shortly after the start and settled well off the pace, bid nearing the three eighths pole, improved at the rail on the far turn and dueled through the stretch for second while gaining on the winner. EX RATED was shuffled back shortly after the break and saved ground well off the pace, bid nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and was just up for third while outfinished for second. MAY MAYS CASTLE took the lead at the thirteen sixteenths pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, dug in under steady handling leaving the turn but was caught flattening stride past the sixteenth pole. PEARLY GHOST angled in and stalked two deep, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. WAGER WORTHY ducked in leaving the gate then angled out, saved ground just off the early pace, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and weakened in the lane. HERETODAYGONMANANA raced off the rail on the first turn then faded through the backstretch. SARAH'S WARRIOR rounded the first turn in the three and four paths and showed little response through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Tennis Tap
ENTRY.COMMENT: shut off early,off rail,bid 3/8,rail far turn,dueled 2nd,gaining

ENTRY.NAME: My Sister Pam
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid 3/8,off rail turn,up past 1/16,edged clear

ENTRY.NAME: May Mays Castle
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured near 1/4,rail turn,caught inside 1/16

ENTRY.OWNER: Mountain View Racing LLC and Golden Melinda B

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: O'CONNER SUNSET was forced outward and into Tempestivo leaving the gate, raced in the five path on the first turn then closed to the lead at the five sixteenths pole, dueled clear past the quarter and was steadily handled in the lane. HOME SCHOOL stalked off the rail on the opening turn, picked up the chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole, raced in range of the lead in the three path on the far turn then dueled through the stretch for second. INFINITE SERIES raced in the four path the first turn then stalked into the backstretch, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. TEMPESTIVO was bumped off stride at the break then saved ground, eased out into the backstretch and bid approaching the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and flattened the final sixteenth. MAKIN' GOLD veered out leaving the gate and settled in the three path the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and showed little in the lane. GOLDEN ADAGE set the early pace inside, came under pressure toward the three eighths pole, was met at the five sixteenth, dropped back into the far turn and flattened at the rail. FLOOR IT saved ground. MONEY MAC rounded the first turn about the six path and showed little response through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Makin' Gold
ENTRY.COMMENT: came out break,off pace 3p,chased 7/16,off rail turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 97. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 31500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER SINCE DECEMBER 16, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 16 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 16 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUAD'DIB stalked inside, started a bid leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, eased around HERO'S MAN entering the stretch and dug in to get up the final yards. The latter took a quick lead and rated the pace inside, came under pressure past the seven sixteenths pole and maintained a clear advantage at the rail on the far turn, dug in under steady handling leaving the turn but gave up the lead in the final yards. FANCY CONCHO rated close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path then flattened the final sixteenth. COMMAND THE CAT rated close two deep, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole but flattened inside the eighth pole. BUBBA GRUMP was unprepared for the start and broke in the air, settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, entered the far turn near the rail but angled to the six path toward the head of the lane and showed little more. BOASTER saved ground. SHAMELESS RISK rated close in the four path the first turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the three path of the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Hero's Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 7/16,clear rail turn,caught late

ENTRY.NAME: Muad'dib
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside,bid 3/8,rail far turn,up final yards

ENTRY.NAME: Shameless Risk
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 15200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 16, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since December 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LITTLE BIT OF THAT took the lead leaving the chute and set a clear pressured pace, widened at the rail on the turn and was kept alert through the stretch. FORTES gave chase through the backstretch, improved at the rail on the turn and cleared second past the eighth pole. INCLUDE THE BEAST chased, raced two deep on the turn, angled to the six path entering the stretch and came along for third later yards. SISTER'S DUTY chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn then flattened inside the eighth pole. THUNDER PUNCH gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. CAPTAIN SAM chased toward the outside, rounded the turn in the five and six paths then weakened. SCARLET TANAGER was never a factor. SALTY SAUL was not a factor. SUPER WILDCAT became anxious in the gate then saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Little Bit of That
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: clear pace,widened rail turn,kept alert lane

DIAL HER raced well off the pace in the three path the first turn, bid past the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the five path, dug in leaving the turn and got up for second the final strides. SKYFLY saved ground close to the pace, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and was nipped from second in the final strides. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Purse 31600. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. (Races Where Entered For $15, 000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANGE YOUR LUCK tapered in and took over nearing the three quarter pole then rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and held on well with steady handling. JUBA BOUND rated close inside, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the far turn but was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. LOGSTRADAMUS saved ground, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then flattened later yards. NEVERFOLD saved ground well off the early pace, bid nearing the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and finished well while passing rivals. HAZEDNCONFUSED raced in the three path the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole and rounded the far turn about the five path, ran evenly to late stretch then flattened stride. REATA'S CASTLE came through the opening turn about the four path and showed little response through the backstretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 17500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOLY DELITE engaged in close chase through the backstretch, took the lead at the rail approaching the top of the stretch, raced clear into the lane and held well under steady handling.
